race.comment: STARLIGHT RIOT (2) got the job done again after running them ragged making it four on end, scoring at this track over 342m (19.48). Winner at her latest appearance in the quickest time on the card. Form reads well for this. PRIME VOLTAGE (1) boasts a strong record this journey here with four wins and three minors from 10 tries. Was out of the placings last time (23.49) at Gawler in a Free For All, finishing fifth and beaten 11 lengths. Can feature with the right run. GRAND CHIEF (5) quickly into stride to win over the 400m at Gawler two runs back then raced on speed again when finishing third at this track last start. Has good box speed and can overcome the tricky draw. Can measure up. BOBCAT CHEVY (4) can sneak into the finish while fresh.
